81% interest in our safety screening and detection business, ge homeland protection, inc., to safran. our remaining security business was sold in the first quarter of 2010. prior to its sale, it offered security and life safety technologies,
including intrusion and access control, video surveillance and sensor monitoring equipment, fire detection and real estate and property control. these businesses are reported in ge corporate items and eliminations.
