businesses, including our security business; results of our insurance activities remaining in continuing operations; cost of our principal pension plans; underabsorbed corporate overhead; and certain non-allocated amounts described below. corporate
items and eliminations is not an operating segment. rather, it is added to operating segment totals to reconcile to consolidated totals on the financial statements.  certain amounts included in corporate items and eliminations cost are not allocated to ge operating segments because they are excluded from the measurement of their operating performance for internal purposes. in
