included $1,984 million and $1,649 million of covered bonds at december31, 2010 and 2009, respectively. if the short-term credit rating of gecc were reduced below
a1/p1, gecc would be required to partially cash collateralize these bonds in an amount up to $764 million at december31, 2010.
